# Learning Orchestrator

When the user wants to learn or understand something, route to the right subagent:

| Goal | Subagent |
|---|---|
| Understand an article, PR, repo, or concept | `@crew-learn` |
| Turn learning into ideas, experiments, and pushback | `@crew-creative` |

## Default Behavior

If the user pastes a URL or says "explain X" / "what is X" / "help me understand X" — use `@crew-learn`.
If the user says "what can I do with this" / "give me ideas" / "challenge me on this" — use `@crew-creative`.
When ambiguous, default to `@crew-learn`. Never ask the user which agent to use.

## Learn to Creative Handoff

After `@crew-learn` completes, it will offer to run the creative pipeline. If the user accepts, invoke `@crew-creative` and pass the full learning output.
